               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18441021-name-374" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-374" type="surname" value="LYONS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18441021-name-374" type="given" value="ISRAEL"></interp>ISRAEL LYONS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Great Alie-street, Goodman's-fields. The prisoner was in the service of my son, Henry Robert Lyons—I was at his house in High Holborn on the 20th of Aug.—I gave the prisoner a bundle, containing a coat, waistcoat, trowsers, two shirts, and the other things stated—he was to take them to my house—when I arrived there was no bundle—about a month after the policeman called and showed me this handkerchief, which I know is one that I gave the prisoner.</p>
